@armouredskeptic  I dont, ive had my own NDES and overdoses and past qith spirituality outside of Christianity; and the people i know IRL wirh nde expierences that ive literally BEEN there for...I just never met someone who had an NDE and it  was all godly and Christian irl. Only ever on documentaries and on grifty Christian podcast; 

Im not saying they're not possible I 100% believe it's possible and something happens to our energy (personal belief) but the whole jesus stuff... just so antithetical to any of the NDES ive actually had. 

To me, these sound like stories of ppl who ARE Christian and DID have an NDE expierence and their mind being in a culture of Christianity and Catholicism is predisposed to Christian imagery, leading to the perception that the NDES are Christian. 

However I have had ndes, and im not christian; i had seen imagry and astral projected during the moments too; but my imagery was more related to my life than christian imagery. If I h ad been predisposed to christian belief systems (was raised christian but was actively asking questions and skeptical since like 7 yo) then I believe my imagery would have been THAT. Its like your brains flashing thoughts to you to comfort you through death. Thats what every NDE uve had felt like. And it makes sense with our brains seeing their final moment; it throws bliss and happy thoughts at the walls. If you believe god is a happy sinless life and thats the answer, then THATS what you see. But I never found comfort in that stuff, only fearmongering; so my brain showed me what comforted ME. 

Just my two cents!

